"12:22:3" : {s: 12, a: 22, w: 3, r: "شدد", t: "أَشُدَّهُۥٓ", l: "أَشُدّ", lc: 8, tl: "ashuddahu", lb: "শক্তি, বল, প্রাপ্ত বয়স, সাবাকত্ব",e: "his maturity", b: "পরিপক্ক বয়সে", i: "dewasanya", f: 5, rm: "to bind tightly, strap, strengthen firmly, run, establish, make firm, hard, strong, be advanced (day), be intense. ushdud - harden, strengthen. shadiid (pl. shidaad & ashiddau - great, firm, strict, vehement, strong, violent, severe, mighty, terrible, stern, grievous, miserly, niggardly. (adj. of the forms faiil and fiaal are used indifferently for both m. and f.): ashuddun: age of full strength, maturity. ishtadda (vb. 8) - to act with violence, become hard."},
